ck |date=21 July 2011 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2011/07/22/world-of-tanks-review |title=World of Tanks Review (PC) |website=IGN |publisher=Ziff Davis |accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n| IGN_X360 = 8/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Butts |first=Steve |date=25 March 2014 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2014/03/26/world-of-tanks-xbox-360-edition-review |title=World of Tanks: Xbox 360 Edition Review |website=IGN |publisher=Ziff Davis |accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n| OXMUK_X360 = 7/10<ref>{{cite magazine |title=World of Tanks: Xbox 360 Edition |magazine=[[Official Xbox Magazine|Official Xbox Magazine UK]] |publisher=Future plc |date=June 2014 |page=84}}</ref>\n| PCGUK_PC = 85%<ref>{{cite magazine |title=World of Tanks |magazine=[[PC Gamer|PC Gamer UK]] |publisher=Future plc |date=June 2011 |page=96}}</ref>\n| TA_iOS = {{rating|4.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://toucharcade.com/2014/07/08/world-of-tanks-blitz/ |title='World of Tanks Blitz' Review \u2013 A Fine Addition To Wargaming's Cannon Canon |last=Musgrave |first=Shaun |date=8 July 2014 |website=[[TouchArcade]] |accessdate=27 July 2019}}</ref>\n| USG_XONE = 4/5<ref>{{cite web |last=Rignall |first=Jaz |date=11 August 2015 |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/world-of-tanks-xbox-one-review |title=World of Tanks Xbox One Review: Thinking Man's Shooter |website=[[Eurogamer|USgamer]] |publisher=Gamer Network |accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[Common Sense Media]]\n| rev1_PC = 4/5<ref>{{cite web |last=Rinaldi |first=Frank |year=2011 |url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/game-reviews/world-of-tanks |title=World of Tanks (PC) |website=[[Common Sense Media]] |accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref>\n| MC_iOS = 83/100<ref name=\"mcios\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/world-of-tanks-blitz |title=World of Tanks Blitz for iPhone/iPad Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref>\n| MC_PC = 80/100<ref name=\"mc\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/world-of-tanks |title=World of Tanks for PC Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>\n| MC_PS4 = 80/100<ref name=\"mcps4\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/world-of-tanks |title=World of Tanks for PlayStation 4 Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n| MC_X360 = 77/100<ref name=\"mc360\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/world-of-tanks-xbox-360-edition |title=World of Tanks: Xbox 360 Edition for Xbox 360 Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>\n| MC_XONE = 76/100<ref name=\"mcxone\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/world-of-tanks |title=World of Tanks for Xbox One Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n<!-- Awards -->\n| award1Pub = [[Golden Joystick Awards|Golden Joystick Awards 2018]]\n| award1    = \"''Still Playing''\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheridan |first=Connor |date=16 November 2018 |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/golden-joystick-awards-2018-winners/ |title=Golden Joystick Awards 2018 winners: God of War wins big but Fortnite gets Victory Royale |website=[[GamesRadar+]] |publisher=Future plc |accessdate=17 November 2018}}</ref>\n| award2Pub = [[Golden Joystick Awards|Golden Joystick Awards 2017]]\n| award2    = \"''Still Playing''\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Dwan |first=Hannah |date=18 November 2017 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/news/2017-golden-joystick-awards-winners-have-revealed/ |title=The 2017 Golden Joystick Awards winners have been revealed |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |accessdate=21 November 2017}}</ref>\n| award3Pub = [[Golden Joystick Awards|Golden Joystick Awards 2013]]\n| award3    = \"''Best Online Game''\"<ref>{{cite web |author=GamesRadar+ staff |date=25 October 2013 |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/watch-our-golden-joystick-awards-livestream-3pm-bst/ |title=Here are your Golden Joystick Award winners 2013 |website=GamesRadar+ |publisher=Future plc |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n| award4Pub = [[Golden Joystick Awards|Golden Joystick Awards 2012]]\n| award4    = \"''Best MMO''\"\n| award5Pub = MMOSITE's Reader's Choice Awards 2010\n| award5    = \"''Most Anticipated MMO in 2010''\"\n| award6Pub = [[Russian Game Developer's Conference|KRI 2010]]\n| award6    = \"''Best Online Client Game''\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldoftanks.com/news/kri_2010_results |title=Make it two in a row! |website=World of Tanks |publisher=Wargaming |date=18 May 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100524183402/http://www.worldoftanks.com/news/kri_2010_results |archivedate=24 May 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=IGN staff |date=18 May 2010 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2010/05/18/wargamingnet-wins-best-kri-2010-game-developer-award-from-critics-in-russia |title=Wargaming Wins Best KRI 2010 Game Developer Award from Critics in Russia |website=IGN |publisher=Ziff Davis |accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n| award7Pub = [[Electronic Entertainment Expo 2010|E3 2010]]\n| award7    = \"''Best New Concept''\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Schuster |first=Shawn |date=19 June 2010 |url=https://www.engadget.com/2010/06/19/massivelys-best-of-e3-2010/ |title=Massively's Best of E3 2010 |website=Engadget (Joystiq) |publisher=Oath Inc. |accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''World of Tanks'' (and the iOS version of ''World of Tanks Blitz'') received \"generally favorable reviews\" on all platforms according to the [[Review aggregator|review aggregation]] website [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"mcios\"/><ref name=\"mc\"/><ref name=\"mcps4\"/><ref name=\"mc360\"/><ref name=\"mcxone\"/> GameZone gave the PC version a score of eight out of ten and stated, \"For a free-to-play game, ''World of Tanks'' is insanely detailed and has combat that takes a while to get used to. The more you learn about the game and the more you play, the better you'll become at it. It's like an investment\u2014spend time playing and you'll be able to upgrade more and compete better. In that sense, the game really drives you towards becoming better. Since it's free, it doesn't hurt to try this game out if you haven't already. Just make sure you get past the growing pains and give it a chance, because it really does have a lot to offer.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Liebl |first=Lance |date=13 December 2011 |url=https://www.gamezone.com/reviews/world-of-tanks-review/ |title=World of Tanks Review (PC) |website=GameZone |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120225165454/http://www.gamezone.com/products/world-of-tanks/reviews/world-of-tanks-review |archivedate=25 February 2012 |url-status=live |accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref> In Japan, ''[[Famitsu]]'' gave the Xbox 360 version a score of one eight, one six, and two sevens for a total of 28 out of 40.<ref name=\"Fam\"/>\n\n=== Userbase ===\n{{Update section|date=April 2019}}\nAccording to a Wargaming official press release from September 2010, the number of ''World of Tanks'' users worldwide reached 700,000, including 500,000 users on Russian servers (350,000 active players), and 200,000 on Western servers (150,000 active players). The number of peak [[concurrent user]]s exceeded 43,000 on Russian servers and 10,000 on Western servers. The average active gamer spent 3 hours 20 minutes playing the game every day; over 10,000,000 battles have been fought since September 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wargaming.net/news.php|title=World of Tanks Reaches Half Million Active Players|date=16 November 2010|publisher=[[Wargaming.net]]|accessdate=8 March 2011}}</ref> By January 2011, ''World of Tanks'' had recorded more than one million registrations worldwide (Europe, Russia and the United States). This milestone was reached in less than a year since the launch of the closed beta in Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.worldoftanks.ru/news/common/million_registrations|title=\u041a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u0432 World of Tanks \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u044b\u0441\u0438\u043b\u043e 1 000 000 \u043f\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u0443|date=4 January 2011|publisher=WorldOfTanks.ru|language=Russian|accessdate=8 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2011-01-04-world-of-tanks-boasts-one-million-users|title=World of Tanks Boasts One Million Users|date=4 January 2011|publisher=Eurogamer.net|accessdate=17 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.worldoftanks.ru/news/common/millions_of_players|date=18 January 2011|publisher=WorldOfTanks.ru|language=Russian|script-title=ru:\u0412 \"\u041c\u0438\u0440\u0435 \u0442\u0430\u043d\u043a\u043e\u0432\" \u043d\u0430 \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u044f\u0437\u044b\u0447\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0438\u0433\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043c \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0441\u044f \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c|accessdate=8 March 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 January 2011 there were 74,536 players simultaneously online on the Russian ''World of Tanks'' server, which, according to Wargaming, had become a world record amongst MMO games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.worldoftanks.ru/news/common/record_number_of_players|date=4 January 2011|publisher=WorldOfTanks.ru|language=Russian|script-title=ru:\"\u041c\u0438\u0440 \u0442\u0430\u043d\u043a\u043e\u0432\" \u0443\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043b \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0434|accessdate=8 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamershell.com/news_108850.html|title=World of Tanks Sets New PCCU Record|date=6 January 2011|publisher=GamersHell.com|accessdate=17 March 2011}}</ref> The \"Most players online simultaneously on one MMO server\" world record was officially registered by [[Guinness World Records]] on 23 January 2011 and constituted 91,311 players.<ref name=\"guinness\">{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/search/Details/Most-players-online-simultaneously-on-one-MMO-server/74482.htm|title=Most players online simultaneously on one MMO server|date=8 March 2011|publisher=GuinnessWorldRecording 500,000 concurrent players on}}</ref>  On 24 May 2011 total number of registrations for all three game servers reached 3 million players (2 million on Russian server and 1 million on Europe and North America).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldoftanks.com/en/news/17/new_milestone/|title=A New Milestone!|website=worldoftanks.com}}</ref>\n\nAs of December 2013, the game has 75{{nbsp}}million registered players worldwide and a 1.1 million peak concurrent players.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geek.com/games/world-of-warcraft-peaked-at-12-million-players-world-of-tanks-just-passed-75-million-1579885/|title=World of Warcraft peaked at 12 million players, World of Tanks just passed 75 million|last=Humphries|first=Matthew|date=16 December 2013|website=Geek.com}}</ref> This is an increase of 15 million over the 60 million in June 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/06/07/world-of-tanks-hits-60-million-registered-users/|title=World of Tanks hits 60 million registered players|last=Grubb|first=Jeffrey|date=7 June 2013|website=[[VentureBeat]]}}</ref> and 30 million over the 45 million in December 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/world-of-tanks-tops-league-of-legends-with-45-million-players/|title=World of Tanks tops League of Legends with 45 million players|last=Agnello|first=Anthony John|date=21 December 2012|website=[[Digital Trends]]|publisher=Designtechnica}}</ref> In June 2013, Wargaming stated that they now have 60 million registered users for ''World of Tanks''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldoftanks.com/en/news/19/world-tanks-hits-mark-60-million-registered-users/|title=World of Tanks Hits the Mark at 60 Million Registered Users|website=worldoftanks.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Revenue ===\n{{Update section|date=April 2019}}In 2012, Wargaming's revenue was declared to be 217.9 million euro, with net profit of 6.1 million euro, as declared in an annual report for the [[Cyprus Stock Exchange]]. The money gained by Wargaming largely came from ''World of Tanks''.<ref>2013-05-07, [http://www.newsru.com/finance/07may2013/woft.html \u0421\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c World of Tanks \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u043b \u0437\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0434 218 \u043c\u043b\u043d \u0435\u0432\u0440\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0442\u0443\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0431\u0438\u0442\u0432\u0430\u0445], NEWSru</ref> In 2013, the microtransaction revenue of ''World of Tanks'' surpassed that of ''[[World of Warcraft]]'', earning $372 million and ranking fourth highest amongst online game revenues.<ref>2014-01-20, [http://en.ria.ru/business/20140120/186729656/Belarusian-Game-Out-Guns-World-of-Warcraft-on-Revenue.html Belarusian Game Out-Guns World of Warcraft on Revenue], Ria Novosti</ref><ref>2014-01-19, [http://www.gamespot.com/articles/league-of-legends-revenues-for-2013-total-624-million/1100-6417224/ League of Legends revenues for 2013 total $624 million], Gamespot</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* ''[[War Thunder]]''\n* ''[[Armored Warfare]]''\n{{Portal bar|Tanks|video games}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n\n* {{Official website|https://worldoftanks.com/}}\n* {{moby game|id=/windows/world-