avorite Movie Actor'''\n| {{nominated}}\n| \n|\n| \n|-\n| '''Favorite Female Voice in an Animated Movie'''\n| \n| {{Pending}}\n|\n| \n|-\n| '''Favorite Male Voice in an Animated Movie'''\n| \n| {{Pending}}\n|\n| \n|}\n\n===Visual Effects Society Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:left;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:214px;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Award\n! colspan=\"2\" | Main series\n! colspan=\"2\" | Spin-offs\n|-\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Movie''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.visualeffectssociety.com/ayear/13th-annual-ves-awards|title=13th Annual VES Awards|work=visual effects society|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part''<ref name=THR>{{cite news|work=Hollywood Reporter|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/lists/2020-visual-effects-society-awards-nominations-full-list-1265672|title=Baby Yoda, Alita, Simba Among VFX Society Awards Nominees|access-date=January 7, 2020 |archive-url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/lists/2020-visual-effects-society-awards-nominations-full-list-1265672|archive-date=January 7, 2020 |url-status=live|df= }}</ref>\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Batman Movie'' <ref name=\"VESA HR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-visual-effects-society-awards-nominations-list-full-1067888|title=Visual Effects Society Awards: 'Apes,' 'Blade Runner 2049' Lead Feature Nominees|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Carolyn|last=Giardina|date=January 16, 2018|accessdate=January 16, 2018}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Ninjago Movie''<ref name=\"VESA HR\" />\n|-\n| '''[[Visual Effects Society Award for Outstanding Visual Effects in an Animated Feature|Outstanding Visual Effects in an Animated Feature]]'''\n| {{nom}} \n| {{nom}} \n| {{nom}} \n| {{nom}} \n|}\n\n===Producers Guild of America===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:left;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:214px;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Award\n! colspan=\"2\" | Main series\n! colspan=\"2\" | Spin-offs\n|-\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Movie'' \n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Batman Movie'' \n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The LEGO Ninjago Movie''\n|-\n| '''[[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Animated Motion Picture]]'''\n| {{Won}}\n|\n| {{nominated}}\n|\n|}\n\n==In other media==\n===Video games===\n====''The Lego Movie Videogame'' (2014)====\n{{Main|The Lego Movie Videogame}}\n''The Lego Movie Videogame'' is the first video game in the franchise, and is loosely based on the 2014 film. The game was developed by [[TT Fusion]], [[TT Games]], and [[Feral Interactive]] (for [[macOS]]), and published by [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]]. It features over 100 playable characters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/wikis/the-lego-movie-video-game/Characters|title=Characters - The LEGO Movie Videogame Wiki Guide - IGN|website=IGN|language=en|access-date=2017-08-31}}</ref>\n\n====''Lego Dimensions'' (2015)====\n{{Main|Lego Dimensions}}\n''Lego Dimensions'' includes characters from various franchises, including ''[[The Lego Movie]]'' and ''[[The Lego Batman Movie]]''.{{citation needed|date=March 2019}} The game's Starter Pack includes Wyldstyle, while Emmet, Benny, Bad Cop, and Unikitty are included in Fun Packs. From ''The Lego Batman Movie'', Robin and Batgirl are included in a Story Pack while Excalibur Batman is included in a Fun Pack.\n\n====''The Lego Batman Movie Game'' (2017)====\nBased on ''[[The Lego Batman Movie]]'', Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment released the [[endless-runner]] game coinciding with the release of the film. It was released for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]].{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n\n====''The Lego Ninjago Movie Video Game'' (2017)====\n{{Main|The Lego Ninjago Movie Video Game}}\nBased on ''[[The Lego Ninjago Movie]]'', Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment released the video game coinciding with the release of the film. It was released for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Nintendo Switch]], [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]].\n\n====''The Lego Movie 2 Videogame'' (2019)====\n{{Main|The Lego Movie 2 Videogame}}\nBased on ''The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part'', the next videogame in the series was announced on November 27, 2018 and was released in North America on February 26, 2019 for the [[PS4]], [[Xbox One]], [[Microsoft Windows]], and [[Nintendo Switch]].{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n\n===Attractions===\n{{Main|The Lego Movie: 4D \u2013 A New Adventure}}\nOn December 16, 2015, a promo video for a new [[4D film]] at [[Legoland Florida]] based on ''The Lego Movie'' called '''''The Lego Movie: 4D \u2013 A New Adventure''''' was posted onto Lego's YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=KHDAeEGxOus|title=The LEGO Movie 4D \u2013 A New Adventure|publisher=YouTube|date=December 16, 2015|accessdate=December 30, 2015}}</ref> The short subject premiered at Legoland Florida on January 29, 2016 before being rolled out to all other [[Legoland|Legoland Parks]] and [[Legoland Discovery Center]]s later that year. It sees many of the original cast returning including [[Elizabeth Banks]] as [[Wyldstyle|Lucy \"Wyldstyle\"]], [[Nick Offerman]] as [[MetalBeard]], [[Alison Brie]] as [[Princess Unikitty]] and [[Charlie Day]] as [[Benny (The Lego Movie)|Benny]] while [[Emmet Brickowski|Emmet]] is voiced by [[A.J. Locascio]] (due to [[Chris Pratt]] being unavailable at the time). The ride introduces a new character, Risky Business (voiced by [[Patton Oswalt]]), who is Lord Business' older brother.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://florida.legoland.com/planning-your-visit/lego-movie-4d-a-new-adventure/|title=\u2018THE LEGO\u00ae MOVIE\u2122 4D A NEW ADVENTURE\u2019 at LEGOLAND Florida Resort|publisher=|accessdate=December 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Lego sets===\n====''The Lego Movie'' Sets====\n{{Main|Lego Minifigures (theme)#The LEGO Movie Series}}\nThe first sets were released in the United States on December 30, 2013 and in the United Kingdom on December 26 that based on the film The Lego Movie with 14 sets being released.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/8339/four-of-the-lego-movie-sets-now-listed |title=Four of The LEGO Movie sets now listed |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2013-11-12}}</ref><ref name=\"The LEGO Movie Set Details\">{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/7938/the-lego-movie-set-details |title=The LEGO Movie Set Details |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2013-10-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/8203/the-lego-movie-sets-are-being-revealed-one-at-a-time-(-spoiler) |title=The LEGO Movie sets are being revealed one at a time (+spoiler) |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2013-11-05}}</ref> The largest of the sets is \"MetalBeard's Sea Cow\" which included 2741 pieces and five minifigures.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/9425/hungarian-site-reveals-summer-lineup |title=Hungarian site reveals summer lineup |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2014-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/10165/metalbeard-s-sea-cow-revealed-at-ny-toy-fair |title=MetalBeard's Sea Cow revealed at NY Toy Fair |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2014-02-16}}</ref> In addition to the sets three polybag sets have been released as promotions are \"The Piece of Resistance\", \"Micro Manager Battle\" and \"Super Secret Police Enforcer\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/9997/the-lego-movie-polybags |title=The LEGO Movie polybags |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2014-02-06}}</ref>\n\nThe second sets were released in the United States on June 3, 2014 and in the United Kingdom on June 1 with 6 sets being released.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/9657/summer-lego-movie-sets |title=Summer LEGO Movie sets |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref><ref name=\"The LEGO Movie Set Details\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/10041/the-lego-movie-sets-screen-time |title=The LEGO Movie: sets screen time |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2014-02-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/12522/2015-the-lego-movie-sets |title=2015 The LEGO Movie sets |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2014-09-28}}</ref> In addition to the sets three polybag sets have been released as promotions are \"Pyjamas Emmet\", \"Radio DJ Robot\" and \"Western Emmet\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/9605/the-lego-movie-polybags |title=The LEGO Movie polybags |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2014-01-10}}</ref>\n\n====''The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part'' Sets====\n{{Main|Lego Minifigures (theme)#The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part Series}}\nThe first sets were released in the United States on January 5, 2019 and in the United Kingdom that based on the film The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part with 17 sets being released.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/37282/three-lego-movie-2-sets-revealed |title=Three LEGO Movie 2 sets revealed |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-07-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/39999/many-more-the-lego-movie-2-the-second-part-sets-unveiled! |title=Many more the LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part sets unveiled! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2018-11-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/40322/new-parts-for-2019! |title=New parts for 2019! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2018-11-29}}</ref> The largest of the sets is \"Rex's Rexplorer!\" which included 1187 pieces and two minifigures.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/41226/the-lego-movie-2-the-second-part-sets-available-now! |title=The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part sets available now! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2018-12-26}}</ref> In addition to the sets five polybag sets have been released as promotions are \"Emmet's 'Piece' Offering\", \"Rex's Plantimal Ambush\", \"Lucy vs. Alien Invader\", \"Mini Master-Building MetalBeard\" and \"Mini Master-Building Emmet\".\n\nThe second sets were released in the United States on April 22, 2019 and in the United Kingdom on May 1 with 6 sets being released.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/42191/three-new-lego-movie-2-sets-revealed! |title=Three new LEGO Movie 2 sets revealed! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-02-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/42526/the-lego-movie-2-development-models |title=The LEGO Movie 2 development models |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/43398/three-summer-sets-from-the-lego-movie-2-now-available-in-north-america! |title=Three summer sets from The LEGO Movie 2 now available in North America! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/44922/interview-with-ilia-gotlib-designer-of-70825-queen-watevra-s-build-whatever-box! |title=Interview with Ilia Gotlib, designer of 70825 Queen Watevra's Build Whatever Box! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-07-27}}</ref> The two largest sets are \"The Rexcelsior!\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/41797/70839-the-rexcelsior-revealed! |title=70839 The Rexcelsior revealed! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-01-22}}</ref> and \"Welcome to Apocalypseburg!\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/41420/70840-welcome-to-apocalypseburg-revealed! |title=70840 Welcome to Apocalypseburg revealed! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-01-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/41679/welcome-to-apocalypseburg-available-now |title=Welcome to Apocalypseburg available now |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-01-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/41719/interview-with-justin-ramsden-and-paul-constantin-turcanu-designers-of-70840-welcome-to-apocalypseburg! |title=Interview with Justin Ramsden and Paul Constantin Turcanu, designers of 70840 Welcome to Apocalypseburg! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2019-01-18}}</ref> In addition to the sets two Magazine Gift sets have been released as promotions are \"Emmet with Tools\" and Rex with Jetpack\".\n\n====''The Lego Batman Movie'' Sets====\n{{Main|Lego Batman|Lego Minifigures (theme)#The LEGO Batman Movie Series}}\nThe first sets were released in the United States on January 2, 2017 and in the United Kingdom on January 1 that based on the film The Lego Batman Movie with 13 sets being released.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/22669/two-lego-batman-movie-sets-revealed |title=Two LEGO Batman Movie sets revealed  |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-07-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/24183/more-the-lego-batman-movie-sets-revealed |title=More The LEGO Batman Movie sets revealed?  |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/24362/more-the-lego-batman-movie-sets-revealed |title=More The LEGO Batman Movie sets revealed |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/24489/even-more-batman-movie-sets-revealed |title=Even more Batman Movie sets revealed |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-11-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/24693/the-lego-batman-movie-cmf-list |title=The LEGO Batman Movie CMF list |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-11-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/24952/images-for-ninety-2017-sets-added-to-lego-com |title=Images for ninety 2017 sets added to LEGO.com |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-11-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/24518/the-lego-batman-movie-official-images |title=The LEGO Batman Movie official images |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-11-13}}</ref> In addition to the sets 8 polybag sets have been released as promotions are \"The Mini Batmobile\", \"Batman in the Phantom Zone\",<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/23965/30522-batman-in-the-phantom-zone-revealed |title=30522 Batman in the Phantom Zone revealed |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2016-10-13}}</ref> \"The Joker Battle Training\", \"The Mini Batwing\", \"The Mini Ultimate Batmobile\", \"Disco Batman - Tears of Batman\", \"Batgirl\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/27545/free-batgirl-polybag-with-tlbm-blu-ray-at-target |title=Free Batgirl polybag with TLBM Blu-ray at Target |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-04-12}}</ref> and \"Bat Shooter\".\n\nThe second sets were released in the United States on June 2, 2017 and in the United Kingdom on June 1 with 5 sets being released<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/26297/summer-tlbm-sets-revealed! |title=Summer TLBM sets revealed! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-01-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/26336/the-return-of-the-movie-maker-set |title=The return of the movie maker set |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-02-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/26378/a-chronological-look-at-the-lego-batmobile |title=A chronological look at the LEGO Batmobile |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-02-03}}</ref> talso included \"The Ultimate Batmobile\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/26537/70917-the-ultimate-batmobile-revealed! |title=70917 The Ultimate Batmobile revealed! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-02-10}}</ref> In addition to the sets 2 polybag sets have been released as promotions are \"Batman Battle Pod\" and \"Accessory pack\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/25789/a-new-year-a-new-lego-movie-and-promotions |title=A new year, a new LEGO movie and promotions |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-01-02}}</ref>\t\n\nThe third sets were released in the United States on January 1, 2018 with 6 sets being released. The largest of the sets is \"The Joker Manor\" which included 3444 pieces and ten minifigures.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/30830/70922-the-joker-manor |title=70922 The Joker Manor |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-09-26}}</ref>\n\n====''The Lego Ninjago Movie'' Sets====\n{{Main|Lego Ninjago|Lego Minifigures (theme)#The LEGO Ninjago Movie Series}}\nThe first sets were released in the United States on August 1, 2017 that based on the film The Lego Ninjago Movie with 15 sets being released.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/27445/first-lego-ninjago-movie-set-revealed! |title=First LEGO NINJAGO Movie set revealed! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/27813/more-the-lego-ninjago-movie-set-details-revealed |title=More The LEGO NINJAGO Movie set details revealed |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-05-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/28566/ninjago-movie-set-piece-counts |title=NINJAGO Movie set piece counts |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-06-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/28666/the-lego-ninjago-movie-set-images |title=The LEGO Ninjago Movie set images |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-06-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/29852/new-lego-ninjago-movie-promotional-material |title=New LEGO NINJAGO Movie promotional material |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/30749/new-the-lego-ninjago-movie-sets-discovered |title=New The LEGO Ninjago Movie sets discovered |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-09-21}}</ref> The largest of the sets is \"NINJAGO City\" which included 4867 pieces and 19 minifigures.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/28766/70620-ninjago-city-revealed! |title=70620 NINJAGO City Revealed! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-06-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/29971/ninjago-city-available-now! |title=NINJAGO City available now! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-08-16}}</ref>\n\nThe second sets were released in the United States on December 2, 2017 with 5 sets being released.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/30753/the-lego-ninjago-movie-wave-2-official-images! |title=The LEGO NINJAGO Movie Wave 2 Official Images! |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-09-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/31458/interview-with-christopher-stamp-ninjago-designer |title=Interview with Christopher Stamp, NINJAGO designer |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-11-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/32342/the-lego-ninjago-movie-wave-two-sets-available-now |title=The LEGO NINJAGO Movie wave two sets available now |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-12-01}}</ref> In addition to the sets 5 polybag sets have been released as promotions are \"Quake Mech\", \"Ice Tank\", \"Green Ninja Mech Dragon\", \"Kendo Lloyd\" and \"Lloyd\".\n\nThe third sets were released in the United States on August 1, 2018 with only one set called \"NINJAGO City Docks\" which included 3553 pieces and 14 minifigures. In addition to the sets 2 polybag sets have been released as promotions are \"Movie Maker\" and \"Kai's Dojo Pod\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/29101/promotional-items-added-to-the-database |title=Promotional items added to the database |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://brickset.com/article/29932/[uk-eu]-free-kai-s-dojo-pod-with-tlnm-sets |title=[UK/EU] Free Kai's Dojo Pod with TLNM sets |publisher=Brickset |accessdate=2017-08-14}}</ref> also included 1 magazine gift called \"Lloyd\".\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Cartoon|Animation|Film|United States|Comedy}}\n{{The Lego Movie}}\n{{Lego}}\n{{Warner Bros. animation and comics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lego Movie}}\n[[Category:The Lego Movie]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. Pictures franchises]]\n[[Category:Universal Pictures franchises]]\n[[Category:Toy franchises]]\n[[Category:Film franchises]]\n[[Category:Lego themes]]\n[[Category:Media franchises introduced in 2014]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure films]]\n[[Category:Comedy film franchises]]\n[[Category:Children's film series]]\n[[Category:Animated film series]]\n[[Category:Film series introduced in 2014]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox media franchise\n| title = The Lego Movie\n| image = The Lego Movie logo.png\n| imagesize = 250px\n| caption = Logo to the first film.\n| creator = {{unbulleted list|Dan Hageman|Kevin Hageman|[[Phil Lord and Christopher Miller|Phil Lord<br />Christopher Miller]]}}\n| origin = ''[[The Lego Movie]]'' (2014)<br />{{based on|[[Lego|Lego Construction Toys]]}}\n| owner = [[The Lego Group|Lego System A/S]]\n| years = 2014\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''''The Lego Movie''''' is a Danish-American [[media franchise]] based on [[Lego]] [[construction toy]]s. It began with the [[The Lego Movie|2014 film of the same name]], which was directed and written by [[Phil Lord and Christopher Miller]]. The success of the film led it to receiving two licensed video games, a [[The Lego Movie: 4D \u2013 A New Adventure|theme park film ride attraction]], two spin-off films which were released in 2017, an [[Unikitty!|animated series]] that also came out in the same year as well as a [[The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part|sequel]] in 2019 among other pieces of media. A third spin-off film as well as a sequel to ''The Lego Batman Movie'' are in development. The films in the franchise have received generally positive critical reception, with the exception of ''Ninjago'' which acquired mixed reviews, and has grossed $1 billion at the worldwide box office. It is produced and owned by Warner Bros. Pictures.\n\n==Films==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Film\n! U.S. <br />release date\n! Director(s)\n! style=\"width:22%;| Screenwriters\n! style=\"width:20%;| Story by\n! Producers\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left\" | ''[[The Lego Movie]]''\n| {{Start date|2014|02|07}}\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Phil Lord and